{{Coord|51.555|0.248|display=title|region:GB_scale:5000}} {{Infobox church |name = St Laurence, Upminster |image = Upminster 021.jpg |caption = |dedication = |denomination = [[Church of England]] ([[Anglican]]) |churchmanship= |parish = |deanery = Havering |archdeaconry = West Ham |diocese = [[Diocese of Chelmsford|Chelmsford]] |province = [[Province of Canterbury|Canterbury]] |vicar = |curate = |verger = |organist = |warden = |website = http://www.upminsterparish.co.uk/ }} The church of '''St Laurence, Upminster''', is the [[Church of England]] parish church in [[Upminster]], England. It is a [[Listed building|Grade I listed building]].<ref name="listing">{{ cite web | url=http://www.havering.gov.uk/index.aspx?articleid=9413 | title= Church of St Laurence, St Mary's Lane, Upminster | publisher=Havering London Borough Council | date= | accessdate= }}</ref> It is the historic [[Minster (church)|minster]] or church from which Upminster derives its name, meaning 'upper church', probably signifying 'church on higher ground'. The place-name is first attested as 'Upmynster' in 1062, and appears as 'Upmunstra' in the [[Domesday Book]] of 1086.
The churchyard contains [[Commonwealth War Graves Commission|war graves]] of six service personnel of [[World War II]].<ref name=cwgc>[http://www.cwgc.org/find-a-cemetery/cemetery/2043463/UPMINSTER%20(ST.%20LAURENCE)%20CHURCHYARD] CWGC Cemetery Report, details from casualty record.</ref>
